' Linear Modus Ponens — presenting the witness σ to a linear-implication
' capability σ ⊸ τ consumes σ exactly once and yields τ. The channel-level
' decomposition is the Rocq lemma lolly_modus_ponens_channel_decomposition;
' the genuine reduction lives in RhoReduction.v / Bisimulation.v.
'
' Source of truth for Figure 5 in docs/theory/cost-accounting-linear-logic.md.
' Render:
'   plantuml -tsvg docs/theory/diagrams/lolly-modus-ponens-sequence.puml

@startuml lolly-modus-ponens-sequence
!theme plain
title Linear modus ponens:  σ ⊗ (σ ⊸ τ) ⊢ τ

actor Deployer as D
participant "Linear zone Δ\n(witness store)" as DELTA
participant "Capability\nσ ⊸ τ" as CAP

D -> DELTA : present witness σ
note right of DELTA : Δ = [σ];  cost req(σ) accounted
D -> CAP : invoke with σ
CAP -> DELTA : consume σ  (consume_linear_atom)
note right of DELTA : Δ = [ ] — σ spent exactly once
CAP --> D : yield τ
note over CAP
  ll_lolly_resource_flow_conservative:
  req(σ ⊸ τ) = req(σ) + req(τ)
  — no resource created ex nihilo
end note
@enduml
